				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">HoH Pet<a name="51523"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 12 04 7:01 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've been grouping w/ a druid regularly in HoH.  She has her DC pet (a wrulon youngling) and it really, really makes the kills go faster.  She has no problem keeping agro from the hasted pet (Crit nukes for 3100 are good for that), so pets going down due to over agro are no problem.
<br />

<br />
I know I can also charm the younglings and those baby armors.  I'm pretty sure I can get them down there safely, too, the same way she does.
<br />

<br />
Here's how I look at it.  I have roughly 2700 mana at level 60. I'll be using my level 39 charm which is 60 mana a pop.  I have FT 5.  I'm sure I can generally get full min duration charms because I'll swap in my wind to do the charms.  So, I shouldn't really lose much mana (5 mana/tick for ft + 1[?] natrual mana regen = 60 mana, the exact cost of my charm).  
<br />
During down time for the druid, I'll swap in my wind again and keep the pet mezzed, so I'm not buring any mana on the charm.  Mana shouldn't be a problem. 
<br />

<br />
So, my question is this: is it worth it?  Pet maxes for 149, average hit is about 96.  That's a substancial increase over my dots (since I'm running w/ the druid singing mana song and selos, I cannot melee).  I think it's a good idea, but it could easily become a headache.
<br />

<br />
Has anyone tried it before?  Had good results?</span></td>
