			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've actually experimented a bit with using the little armours (or wrulon younglings) as an additional 'dot' if I decide to do some lazy HoH chanting. Snag a set or two of mage summoned weapons, single pull your pet-to-be, charm him, and pass him the weapons.  If you're kiting in a decent open area (such as part of GY) then even when charm breaks you would have to be having a really bad day to get hit at all by your ex pet, let alone in any danger from it due to the weapons etc.  
<br />

<br />
Adding a better equipped pet to your chant kite can be quite a noticeable difference as well.  By 65, your charm generally lasts the full 1 min duration on the little guys, and with FT5+, you shouldn't really run out of mana.  Just make sure that your pet and target are both on your target toggle button, and you will only go 3 to 4 seconds with an uncharmed pet anyway.</span></td>
